textBody:
KB, kB or kb may stand for:

Businesses and organizations

Banks 

* KB Kookmin Bank, the largest bank in South Korea
* Kaupthing Bank, a bank in Iceland
* Komerční banka, a bank in the Czech Republic
* Kasikornbank, a bank in Thailand
* Karafarin Bank, a bank in Iran

Libraries 

* National Library of Sweden ()
* National Library of the Netherlands ()

Sport

* Kalix BF, a Swedish bandy club
* Kjøbenhavns Boldklub, a Danish sports club based in Copenhagen

Other businesses and organizations

* KB Home, a major American home builder
* KB Lager, a brand of Australian beer
* KB Toys, a United States toy retail chain
* K&B, a local drug store in New Orleans, Louisiana, that was bought by Rite Aid
* Druk Air (IATA code: KB), the national airline of Bhutan

People

* Kevin Bartlett (Australian rules footballer) (born 1947), former Australian rules footballer
* KB (rapper) (born 1988), stage name of Christian hip hop artist Kevin Elijah Burgess
* Kyle Busch (born 1985), NASCAR driver

Science and technology 

Biology 

* KB (cell line), an oral epidermoid carcinoma cell line

 Computing 

* Kilobit (kb), a unit of information used, for example, to quantify network transmission capacity
* Kilobyte (kB), a unit of information used, for example, to quantify computer memory or storage capacity
* Computer keyboard, an input device for computer
* Knowledge base, used to store complex structured and unstructured information
** Microsoft Knowledge Base,  containing information on problems encountered by users of Microsoft products

Vehicles 

* KB series, a truck produced by International Harvester
* KB is a name used by Isuzu in some markets for two related models: 
** Isuzu Faster, a pickup truck
** Isuzu D-Max, a pickup truck
* NZR KB class, a New Zealand steam locomotive

Other uses in science and technology

* Base dissociation constant (Kb), the equilibrium constant for a base
* Ebullioscopic constant (Kb), which relates molality to boiling point elevation
* Boltzmann constant (kB), the physical constant which relates temperature to energy
* Kilo-base pair (kb or kbp), a unit of measurement of DNA or RNA length used in genetics, equal to 1,000 nucleotides
* Kauri-butanol value (Kb value), a measure of solvent performance

Other uses 

* King's Bench, an ancient English court, or the legal citation denoting a case in such court
* King's Buildings, a campus at the University of Edinburgh, containing most of the schools within the College of Science and Engineering
* Knowledge Bowl, an interdisciplinary academic competition
* Knight of the Bath, a former rank (before 1815) of the Order of the Bath, a part of the British honours system
** sometimes also incorrectly used to refer to Knight Bachelor
* Kuala Belait, a town in Brunei
* WWKB, a radio station often referred to as KB Radio 1520
